✅ STEP 1 — System Preparation

Update system first:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Install basic tools:

sudo apt install -y curl wget git vim python3-pip
✅ STEP 2 — Install Docker (For Kubernetes Lab)
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

Now logout and login again.

Test:

docker --version
✅ STEP 3 — Install kind (Lightweight Kubernetes)

We use
kind

curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/latest/kind-linux-amd64
chmod +x ./kind
sudo mv ./kind /usr/local/bin/kind

Create single-node cluster (important for 8GB):

kind create cluster

Verify:

kubectl get nodes
✅ STEP 4 — Install kubectl (If Not Installed)
sudo snap install kubectl --classic

Add alias for speed (important for CKA):

echo "alias k=kubectl" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
✅ STEP 5 — Install Local AI (Light Model Only)

Install
Ollama

curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

Now pull a SMALL model (important for 8GB):

ollama pull phi3

Run it:

ollama run phi3

Test prompt:

Explain Kubernetes Pod lifecycle in simple terms.

If system becomes slow → close browser tabs.

✅ STEP 6 — Install AI Execution Agent

Install
Open Interpreter

pip install open-interpreter

Run in lightweight mode:

interpreter --local

Test prompt:

Create a simple nginx deployment YAML and save as nginx.yaml







